text: Three ships of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary have borne the name RFA Olna: * was an oiler launched in 1921 and beached at Crete in 1941 after being bombed. * was an oiler launched in 1944 and scrapped in 1967. * was a fast fleet tanker launched in 1965 and sold in 2001. title: RFA Olna
